Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+):

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class HardwareTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public HardwareTests()
    {
        // 4. Create temp file in constructor
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    // 1. Windows-only (skipped on other OS)
    [TestMethod]
    [OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
    public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
    {
        var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\...", "Key", null);
        Assert.IsNotNull(value);
    }

    // 2. Skip in CI (runs only locally)
    [TestMethod]
    [CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
    public void GpuRender_ProducesExpectedOutput()
    {
        var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
        Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    }

    // 3. Flaky external API — retry up to 3 times
    [TestMethod]
    [Retry(3)]
    public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
    {
        var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync();
        Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
    }

    // 4. Cleanup runs even if test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
        {
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
        }
    }
}
```

**Summary of attributes:**

| Scenario | Solution |
|----------|----------|
| Windows-only | `[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]` |
| Skip in CI | `[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]` |
| Flaky external API | `[Retry(3)]` |
| Cleanup on failure | Implement `IDisposable` (or use `[TestCleanup]`) |

**Notes:**
- `[OSCondition]` and `[CICondition]` require MSTest 3.10+
- `[Retry]` requires MSTest 3.9+ — use only for genuinely flaky externals, not to mask race conditions
- `IDisposable.Dispose()` is called after every test regardless of pass/fail, same as `[TestCleanup]` but enables `sealed` classes without inheritance concerns
